    <stitle>13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14613 - REMOVE - CLUTCH HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CLUTCH HOUSING</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For models so equipped, remove the clutch release mechanism and/or clutch brake assembly.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the six bolts, and six nuts and lockwashers from the studs that secure the clutch
                housing to the transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302734">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302734" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302734" filename="../figg13/G1302734.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 34. Remove Bolts, Nuts, and Lockwashers Securing Clutch Housing to Transmission Case
            </caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Jar the clutch housing with a rubber mallet to break the gasket seal and pull from the
                transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302735">Figure 35</hotlnk>). Remove the gasket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302735" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302735" filename="../figg13/G1302735.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 35. Pull Clutch Housing From Transmission Case</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
